      <h1 class='title'>Generic Medicines</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 12 December 2002 vol 396 cc31-2WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_31ws' title='Col. 31WS &mdash; HC Deb 12 December 2002 vol 396 c31WS' name='column_31ws' href='#column_31ws' rel='bookmark'>31WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0396P0_20021212_CWS_17'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-alan-milburn' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0396P0_20021212_CWS_17' title='Link to this speech by Mr Alan Milburn' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-alan-milburn" title="Mr Alan Milburn">The Secretary of State for Health (Mr. Alan Milburn):</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para"> The Government have decided to roll forward, unchanged, the maximum price scheme for generic medicines used in National Health Service primary care. This follows consultation with stakeholders that concluded on 29 November 2002.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_32ws' title='Col. 32WS &mdash; HC Deb 12 December 2002 vol 396 c32WS' name='column_32ws' href='#column_32ws' rel='bookmark'>32WS</a><p>The scheme was introduced in August 2000 as a result of price increases in the generics market that started in 1999. It was rolled forward in October 2001. The scheme has restored stability in the generics market and the NHS has saved some &#x00A3;330 million annually as a result. The continuation of it will ensure that this stability continues and that the expenditure savings are maintained.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
